commit.message:
Correct name of the `selection-to-clipboard` extension

The actual name of the extension is `selection-to-clipboard`, with dashes.
Add option for copying to clipboard too
Move deprecated extensions into subfolder
Allow Home/End keys in selection mode
Make Ctrl-m work as Return in selection.
Scroll before drawing the selection when refreshing; fixes issue #70
Use highlightColor in selection renderings; fixes issue #69
Deprecate url-select
Deprecate clipboard

keyboard-select: Use the same copy method for all selection modes

selection_grab was used to copy block selections. Character and line wise
selections are copied with selection_{beg,end,make}. url-select also uses these
functions for copying.

Using selection_grab seems to not trigger the on_sel_grab hook in the clipboard
extension, which is used for the autocopy feature. Using selection_make does
trigger the hook.

This patch makes keyboard-select always use selection_{beg,end,make} regardless
of the selection mode.

This fixes issue #64.
keyboard-select: Y mapping, copy cursor line and quit; fixes issue #62
Small alignment adjustments

url-select: Unset underline flag after partial redraw

This fixes the behaviour where after redraw of only parts of the line
the underline flag was still being set even though the new line doesn't
match anymore. This can be simulated for example by starting an editor,
typing a URL and changing e.g. the http:// part to xttp:// without
changing the line length (vim: rx) where the part beginning with ttp://
keeps being underlined.

This commit sets the 3rd custom rendition bit (starting at 0) of a cell
iff the underline was being added as a result of the cell being part of
a match. If so, on a line update these underline flags get cleared again
(together with the custom rendition bit) to be then re-set after a
(possible) successful match.
compatibility with urxvt 9.21+
url-select: catch button presses, fixes issue #54

implement incremental search
